\title{SGA 4: Theorie des topos et cohomologie etale des schemas}
\taxon{reference}
\date{1972}
\meta{author}{A. Grothendieck, M. Artin, J.-L. Verdier}

\p{A. Grothendieck, M. Artin, J.-L. Verdier. \em{SGA 4: Theorie des topos et cohomologie etale}. Lecture Notes in Mathematics 269, 270, 305. Springer, 1972--1973. Defines Grothendieck topologies, sites, and sheaf cohomology. The BCI pipeline ([[horse-0002]], [[bci-0001]]) models the electrode montage as a site and the signal as a presheaf.}
